  24:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****   ==============================================================================
  25:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****                         ##### ICACHE main features #####
  26:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****   ==============================================================================
  27:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****   [..]
  28:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     The Instruction Cache (ICACHE) is introduced on C-AHB code bus of
ARM GAS  C:\Users\DELL\AppData\Local\Temp\ccDFnThS.s 			page 2


  29:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     Cortex-M33 processor to improve performance when fetching instruction
  30:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     and data from both internal and external memories. It allows close to
  31:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     zero wait states performance.
  32:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c **** 
  33:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     (+) The ICACHE provides two performance counters (Hit and Miss),
  34:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         cache invalidate maintenance operation, error management and TrustZone
  35:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         security support.
  36:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c **** 
  37:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     (+) The ICACHE provides additionally the possibility to remap input address
  38:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         falling into up to four memory regions (used to remap aliased code in
  39:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         external memories to the internal Code region, for execution)
  40:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c **** 
  41:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****   ===============================================================================
  42:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  43:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****   ===============================================================================
  44:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****   [..]
  45:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****      The ICACHE HAL driver can be used as follows:
  46:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c **** 
  47:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     (#) Optionally configure the Instruction Cache mode with
  48:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         HAL_ICACHE_ConfigAssociativityMode() if the default configuration
  49:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         does not suit the application requirements.
  50:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c **** 
  51:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     (#) Enable and disable the Instruction Cache with respectively
  52:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         HAL_ICACHE_Enable() and HAL_ICACHE_Disable().
  53:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         Use HAL_ICACHE_IsEnabled() to get the Instruction Cache status.
  54:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         To ensure a deterministic cache behavior after power on, system reset or after
  55:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         a call to @ref HAL_ICACHE_Disable(), the application must call
  56:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         @ref HAL_ICACHE_WaitForInvalidateComplete(). Indeed on power on, system reset
  57:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         or cache disable, an automatic cache invalidation procedure is launched and the
  58:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         cache is bypassed until the operation completes.
  59:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c **** 
  60:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     (#) Initiate the cache maintenance invalidation procedure with either
  61:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         HAL_ICACHE_Invalidate() (blocking mode) or HAL_ICACHE_Invalidate_IT()
  62:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         (interrupt mode). When interrupt mode is used, the callback function
  63:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         HAL_ICACHE_InvalidateCompleteCallback() is called when the invalidate
  64:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         procedure is complete. The function HAL_ICACHE_WaitForInvalidateComplete()
  65:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         may be called to wait for the end of the invalidate procedure automatically
  66:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         initiated when disabling the Instruction Cache with HAL_ICACHE_Disable().
  67:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         The cache operation is bypassed during the invalidation procedure.
  68:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c **** 
  69:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     (#) Use the performance monitoring counters for Hit and Miss with the following
  70:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         functions: HAL_ICACHE_Monitor_Start(), HAL_ICACHE_Monitor_Stop(),
  71:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         HAL_ICACHE_Monitor_Reset(), HAL_ICACHE_Monitor_GetHitValue() and
  72:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         HAL_ICACHE_Monitor_GetMissValue()
  73:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c **** 
  74:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****     (#) Enable and disable up to four regions to remap input address from external
  75:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         memories to the internal Code region for execution with
  76:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****         HAL_ICACHE_EnableRemapRegion() and HAL_ICACHE_DisableRemapRegion()
  77:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c **** 
  78:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****   @endverbatim
  79:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_icache.c ****   */
